</CENTER><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95%><TR><TD><B><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Council of Guilds</FONT></A></B><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>CoG Dragon Raids</FONT></A></B><BR><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Sacred Band Dragon Raid Loot Rules</FONT></B></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddTopicScreenFromWeb><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/newTopic.gif border=0></A>&nbsp; <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddPollScreenFromWeb><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/newPoll.gif border=0></A>&nbsp; <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=62.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showMessage?topicID=101.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showMessage?topicID=70.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="95%"><tr><td bgcolor=#000000><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><TR><TD valign=top BGCOLOR=#8E9173><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top BGCOLOR=#8E9173><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#FFFFCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>ezOP</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8E9173>2/1/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8E9173>9:41:38 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Sacred Band Dragon Raid Loot Rules</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Here are the loot policies for the dragon raids. First off, no loot policy will ever be 100% honest-to-goodness fair. Someone will always feel and in some cases will always be given less than their chance to get an item. Fact of life. There will always be exceptions that we cannot forsee which will mean that someone gets slighted. Human nature is one of greed but it can also be one of giving. So with that in mind, here is the loot policy. <br>
<br>
1) No item is worth a friendship. The Gods of Norrath don't drop friends, they drop weapons and stat bonuses and proc effects. Once a friend is lost, no GM can get him/her back. There are no resses for friendships and no to summon 20 stacks of friends. No str or dex or int or mana bonus can ever replace a friend. Always argue with this in mind. <br>
2) No one in your group, your guild or the raiding party pays more or less for their time on Everquest. You are not more or less important than any one else who might have an opportunity at that item. We are all equal and we are all here for each other. By depriving someone else of an item, you are depriving yourself of a friend. <br>
3) All members present at the time the item drops (and those who went linkdead during the fight) who can USE the item (i.e. their class/race combo is on the item) may lotto for the item. Only the character that is being played is to be considered (no twinking secondaries from our raids unless no one else wants the item). The only exceptions to this rule that may be made are to be determined by the raid leader prior to the raid and can include: a) It is used in an important (level of importance determined by the raid leader) quest that a member/members of the raid needs or would like to do. If said item is to be given to ONLY 1 person on the raid (say we get Belce a piece of the warrior epic quest, though there are other warriors on the raid) instead of all lottoing, that should, when possible be announced beforehand, b) the item is not needed by anyone on the raid, and there are those who wish to sell the item, at which point all who wish to do so may lotto on the item.<br>
4) Only group leaders and the designated loot person should loot on raids where items of importance are dropped. Split should be on except in extenuating circumstances (monks in the group, etc.) or unless the group leader prefers to manually split the coin loot. <br>
5) The raid leader/organizer and his/her designated loot person shall be the final word on any raid they lead. Not even guild leaders should call into question the decisions of the raid leader, except in situations where it completely contradicts the spirit of these rules. <br>
6) Preferential treatment based on number of raid attendances shall be not be used. I.e. I'm on my first dragon raid, I will have a chance to get something that drops for my class. <br>
7) Any exceptions to the above should be noted in advance of the raid, at the very least by the raid organizer in his/her pre-raid briefing. <br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     Once an item has been given to a person from a raid, from that point forth the item is considered that person's to do what they wish with it, whether it be use it, give it away, sell it or destroy it. <br>
9) In places where multiple items for a person's class are dropped (i.e. the planes, Karnor's etc.), winning a lotto for one class specific item (or class usable item) puts them out of the lotto for any other class specific items until all of their class have won something. <br>
10) The notable exception to the no secondaries rule is in a situation where someone has 2 characters of fairly equal level (such as a level 40 sk and 42 cleric). If the person is asked to bring one character over another based on need for that class (for instance we need clerics so the cleric is asked). If the raid leader agrees, the cleric may loot for the SK (and therefore lotto for the SK gear) but only at the cost of NOT being in the lotto for his cleric gear. Again, this is the raid leader's decision whether to allow or disallow this, but if it is allowed, it should be announced before the raid. <br>
<br>
Item loot policies can be fair if one thing is kept in mind. We are all here for each other. By helping each other, we help ourselves. Conversely, by hurting each other, we hurt ourselves. The spirit of these rules is to be fair, inclusive instead of exclusive, and above all, to maintain our friendships OVER our desire for better gear. These rules are to be used flexibly, and though fairly firm, are meant to allow change when the situation dictates it, at the discretion of the raid leader. <br>
<br>
On Vox, there is only one no drop/non-quest item, the Dragonbone hammer. In the case of no drop items, we will roll for that item BEFORE the raid with the classes able to use it, just in case the corpse poofs before we get a chance to lotto the item off. <br>
<br>
Haemish MacLennan<br>
